{"key":"processedPost-18584184","value":{"id":18584184,"first":18582702,"last":18598008,"when":1374334941,"utime":"07/20/13 06:42 PM","cleanedPost":"That's what we call 'split' caps as opposed to 'cracked' caps.&nbsp; Split caps are caused by growing too fast where the cells can't expand fast enough to hold all the water being pumped in.<br />Cracked caps more resemble the cracks on a turtle or horned toads back, and are caused by too low a humidity.&nbsp; Cracked caps can actually improve food quality and are often deliberately produced with shiitake by subjecting them to a constantly fluctuating humidity between 10% and 90%.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/13-29/433479745-Dried-White-Flower-Shiitake-Mushroom.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/13-29/433479745-thumb_Dried-White-Flower-Shiitake-Mushroom.jpg\"></a>"}}